text:
This one is definitely the most Zelda to me, of all the pieces you've made. Wind Waker style, for sure. I love the intensity, coupled with the quiet rhythm that plays behind it. Its soft and enticing, yet keeps you on edge.
MakeMeMad31 commented on how it sounds like DKC, and I agree with that too. It could definitely find a place in Donkey Kong Country Returns. NIce work, Supra!

text:
I think that this concept is very cool. I always wanted to do this in a Zelda that was futuristic, where Ganon is the boss of the most menacing crime mob in Hydia. [i know, weird :p]

Temple/level 1[Downtown Rooftops] The dark downtown rooftops of the metropolis (Hydia) This has many people to fight.
Temple/level2-[The Sewers] whatever you expect in the sewers you'll fight there
Temple/level3-[The lab] an animal mutation lab
Temple/level4-[Some corporate building] a building taken over by Ganon.
author: DCombz

text: very nice work indeed SD. One thing you should add to your list of things to keep in mind when writing these tunes is the fact that the player will be trying to solve puzzles throughout the dungeon to proceed deeper and the music tends to be intriguing to reflect this mentality. This tune definitely hit that mark, especially in the drums and percussion. Just something to keep in mind for the future :)

text:
I can just imagine this being played on an underground torch-lit cavern with aborigine paintings/architecture, just something really epic. It'd gradually look faker as you progressed until you ended up in some children's playroom type setting to totally contrast the music, and the music would keep playing because the room is eerily empty. At first, I was thinking of Akira actually.
